<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="100" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="11" pageNumber="100">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="11" pageNumber="100">
<taxonomicName authority="K.Romaschenko, P.M.Peterson &amp; R.J.Soreng, 2019" authorityName="K.Romaschenko, P.M.Peterson &amp; R.J.Soreng" authorityYear="2019" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Pseudoeriocoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pseudoeriocoma" order="Poales" pageId="11" pageNumber="100" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="100">Pseudoeriocoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Eriocoma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eriocoma" order="Poales" pageId="11" pageNumber="100" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="100">Eriocoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Nutt. in having bamboo-like culms commonly with up to 13 nodes, 3-6 mm thick below, with ramified branching at the middle and upper nodes.
</paragraph>
